{{defn|no=2|1=The [[Normal bundle#Algebraic geometry|normal cone]] to ''X'' is <math>\operatorname{Spec}_X(\oplus_0^{\infty} I^n/I^{n+1})</math>. if ''X'' is regularly embedded into ''Y'', then the normal cone is isomorphic to <math>\operatorname{Spec}_X(\mathcal{S}ym(I/I^2))</math>, the total space of the normal bundle to ''X''.}}

